You Answer  Chuni GoswamiFormer footballerThe idea is laudable. There could be some resistance to the implementation of the penalty in the begining. If we try to impose it with punitive measures, it may not be a success overnight but it will create awareness among the public. That in itself is a gain to start with. If we continue the drive sincerely, it is sure to succeed. The drive can start in places like shopping malls and stadiums where people assemble and there are security personnel to impose the penalty.  Copyright 
